article.headline: Cent Connecticut 79, Wagner 54
article.story: NEW BRITAIN, Conn. (AP) -- Tristan Blackwood scored 28 points and Central Connecticut beat Wagner 79-54 Monday night to end the regular season undefeated at home in conference play. Obie Nwadike added 18 points and 14 rebounds for the Blue Devils (19-11, 16-2 Northeast Conference). Joe Seymore chipped in 14 points and Javier Mojica added 12. Central, which clinched the regular-season conference title on Feb. 15, never trailed. The Blue Devils opened the game on an 14-4 run, feeding off three blocked shots from Jemino Sobers. Blackwood, who was coming off a career-high 40 point effort last Thursday against Robert Morris, scored 16 first-half points, hitting four of seven from 3-point range as Central took a 33-23 lead into intermission. The Blue Devils stretched that to 58-38 halfway through the second half on a dunk by Nwadike and cruised from there. Blackwood was 10 of 15 from the floor and hit six of 11 from behind the arc. He also had seven assists. Wagner (11-18, 8-10) was led by James Ulrich, who had 14 points, and played almost a minute in the second half after losing one shoe before officials stopped play. The Seahawks shot just 32 percent from the field. Central has now won 17 consecutive regular-season conference games at Detrick Gym, including all nine conference games this season. They open the conference tournament at home on Thursday.
